I'm speaking softly

1544
01:50:01,969 --> 01:50:04,304
I say the things that
I think Muhammad would say.

1545
01:50:05,539 --> 01:50:06,373
Prophet

1546
01:50:06,607 --> 01:50:08,342
Muhammad has taught us that

1547
01:50:08,575 --> 01:50:11,011
we don't even understand,
we could never comprehend

1548
01:50:11,011 --> 01:50:15,182
the value of taking care of the ill or
providing for the dying

1549
01:50:15,516 --> 01:50:17,284
maintaining their dignity.

1550
01:50:18,652 --> 01:50:22,489
And I believe that that's my mission,
to be the helper, to be the listener

1551
01:50:23,490 --> 01:50:25,792
to be a comforter in many ways.

1552
01:50:34,468 --> 01:50:37,738
The Prophet knew that death was coming

1553
01:50:37,971 --> 01:50:41,575
he had an indication that he would not be
around for much longer.

1554
01:50:42,543 --> 01:50:46,580
MUHAMMAD had been feeling ill.
He'd had some fever.

1555
01:50:47,381 --> 01:50:52,719
It was clear that he was in real difficulty
in terms of his health.

1556
01:50:53,420 --> 01:50:58,025
And the household seemed to be convinced that
MUHAMMAD was dying.

1557
01:50:59,126 --> 01:51:01,061
And while he was on his deathbed

1558
01:51:01,662 --> 01:51:06,533
and there were many who surrounded him,
especially his close companions and his family

1559
01:51:07,134 --> 01:51:10,537
he called for silence around him.

1560
01:51:11,004 --> 01:51:16,476
And he wanted it to be a time of quiet and
of peace and of calm.

1561
01:51:17,878 --> 01:51:21,582
Embraced by the community
he had founded in Medina and

1562
01:51:21,582 --> 01:51:24,151
cared for by his wives and companions

1563
01:51:24,451 --> 01:51:29,389
Muhammad died peacefully on
June 8th, in the year 632.

1564
01:51:31,525 --> 01:51:34,962
The news of his death shocked
his followers, especially Umar

1565
01:51:35,262 --> 01:51:38,031
who believed Muhammad
would outlive them all.

1566
01:51:38,699 --> 01:51:41,201
People began to hear
the Prophet is dead.

1567
01:51:41,568 --> 01:51:47,140
Umar went to the center square and
started to say

1568
01:51:48,041 --> 01:51:52,446
there are hypocrites and liars who are
saying that the Prophet is dead.

1569
01:51:53,680 --> 01:51:59,486
In the midst of this chaos, Abu Bakr reminded
the Muslims of a verse from the Quran

1570
01:51:59,486 --> 01:52:02,890
that had first been revealed
after the battle of Uhud

1571
01:52:03,323 --> 01:52:06,393
when they feared that Muhammad
had been killed.

1572
01:52:07,828 --> 01:52:10,497
Abu Bakr,
comes into this scene of pandemonium.

1573
01:52:10,898 --> 01:52:15,836
And he immediately, uh,
stands up and says

1574
01:52:16,103 --> 01:52:20,207
whoever worshipped Muhammad, uh,
then know that Muhammad is dead.

1575
01:52:20,574 --> 01:52:25,946
But whoever worshipped God,
know that God lives on and never dies.

1576
01:52:26,180 --> 01:52:29,650
And so, suddenly these people are
brought to their senses

1577
01:52:30,050 --> 01:52:34,988
that indeed that Muhammad is, is a man.

1578
01:52:34,988 --> 01:52:36,323
And men are mortal.

1579
01:52:36,590 --> 01:52:37,958
And, and this is his legacy.

1580
01:52:38,192 --> 01:52:43,430
He, he did everything within his power
to prevent himself from being worshipped.

1581
01:52:43,430 --> 01:52:49,636
Because he recognized that that was a danger
inherent in religious tradition.

1582
01:52:49,837 --> 01:52:53,941
That the object of worship
becomes the messenger, and not

1583
01:52:54,274 --> 01:52:56,143
uh, the one sending the message.

1584
01:53:07,254 --> 01:53:11,058
Prophet Muhammad was a man,
he was flesh and blood

1585
01:53:11,291 --> 01:53:15,262
who brought one of the most eloquent
revelations to mankind.

1586
01:53:15,629 --> 01:53:17,197
He's set an example

1587
01:53:18,031 --> 01:53:22,569
to mankind through his behavior,
through his actions, a living example.

1588
01:53:23,303 --> 01:53:26,206
This is a legacy that
he has left for Muslims.

1589
01:53:26,874 --> 01:53:30,277
Muhammad's legacy is obviously
the seed that he planted.

1590
01:53:30,344 --> 01:53:34,882
It is his righteousness,
his honesty, his integrity

1591
01:53:35,349 --> 01:53:40,320
his model as uh as a political leader,
his model as an individual

1592
01:53:40,888 --> 01:53:45,492
a man who has uh made great
accomplishments in his time

1593
01:53:45,492 --> 01:53:50,931
and yet who didn't let the successes uh
overpower him

1594
01:53:51,231 --> 01:53:54,134
didn't let his ego get the best of him.

1595
01:53:54,735 --> 01:53:59,206
He remains, I think,
more than anything else a great role model.

1596
01:54:00,474 --> 01:54:03,310
MUHAMMAD is the kind of person

1597
01:54:04,011 --> 01:54:10,717
who combines political and military and
social and religious

1598
01:54:11,018 --> 01:54:15,189
and intellectual dimensions of life
in ways that are important

1599
01:54:15,189 --> 01:54:18,559
for those of us in the 21st century

1600
01:54:18,992 --> 01:54:22,462
who are struggling to put together
complete lives ourselves.

1601
01:54:24,431 --> 01:54:30,938
If I were to have met Prophet Muhammad
on the street, I feel like I would know him.

1602
01:54:31,438 --> 01:54:34,641
And as though he would know all of us.

1603
01:54:36,610 --> 01:54:40,647
The beauty of it is, we live our lives
through his examples, but he's not God.

1604
01:54:41,215 --> 01:54:42,716
Our reverence is to God.

1605
01:54:43,317 --> 01:54:45,185
And our reference is to him.

1606
01:54:46,353 --> 01:54:49,790
So how I walk, and how I speak,
and how I carry myself

1607
01:54:50,457 --> 01:54:53,360
and how I treat my husband, and
how I treat my mother and my father

1608
01:54:53,360 --> 01:54:56,029
and how I behave as a sister and a daughter

1609
01:54:56,029 --> 01:54:58,298
and a nurse and a friend and a neighbor

1610
